data.title: Fox Surf Presents | Caroline Marks Makes history, 2014 Surfing America USA Championships
data.description:
Fox Surf's Caroline Marks made history at the 2014 Surfing America USA Championships at Lower Trestles in Southern California. Caroline also won the Open Women's NSSA National title in Huntington Beach the following week. This is the first time any surfer has won 3 divisions in a USA Championships. Caroline won the Girls 12 Under, 14 Under, and 16 Under divisions. This huge result earned Caroline a spot on the 2014/15 Surfing America Team USA. Congrats Caroline from the Fox family. 

Music- Raye Feagan by Fear Club

Filmed by- Justin Jung and Jensen Young Sik
Edit By Jensen Young Sik

data.title: Fox MX Presents | MX15 The Brotherhood of Motocross
data.description:
Riding a dirt bike is an incredibly unique and special experience. It’s unfortunate that not everyone gets to enjoy it at least once in their lifetime. There is a freedom and thrill to it that is unmatched by anything else. 

The fact that many of us get to do it regularly is a blessing.
There is something even more amazing about sharing the experience of riding with your friends, or with acquaintances who become friends by the end of the day. Whether it’s trails, track or dunes doesn’t matter, what matters is the common bond of the experience of the adventure. It is a soulful experience that can be both life changing, as well as life reaffirming.

As someone who lives this moto life, hopefully you already know the feeling. If not, then search it out and find it for yourself.

data.title: Fox Surf Presents | East Coast We Live Surf Tour
data.description:
This summer the Fox Surf team hit the East Coast in search of stoke and surf. Traveling over 2,000 miles in the Fox Bus, Fox Surf's Ian Walsh, Bruce Irons, Damien Hobgood, Chippa Wilson and Luke and Caroline Marks found little surf but plenty of stoke. Fox Surf teamed up with key retailers and held in store signings, BBQs and fun beach activities while on the East Coast. This video captures the good times retailers and fans shared on the Fox "We Live" Surf Tour."

Music: Tomorrow blues by Judson McKinney I gets my boogie on by T bird and the breaks

Filmed and Edited: Jensen Young Sik

data.title: Fox Wake Presents | Bob Soven We Live | A Tad Unconventional
data.description:
Bob Soven’s approach to life isn’t as much about seizing the moment as it is about letting the moment seize him. Always game for an adventure, new experience, or getting out of his comfort zone, Bob is known for taking life as it comes and making the most out of it. A hobbyist to a fault, Bob hasn’t found something he doesn’t want to try, be it living in a fifth-wheel trailer, bow hunting, free diving, or starring in a reality TV show. While wakeboarding is his passion and career, it has also been his gateway to living the life he wants just the way he wants: without limits or conventional structure.

Edit:
Ryan Marcus
Veesh

Cameras:
Ryan Marcus
Jon Vital

Music:
Two Wooden Stones
"Sold My Soul"
Looking for the Light

Gypsyblood
"Endless Summer"
Cold in the Guestway
Sargent House

data.title: FOXHEAD EUROPE Presents  MXON - LATVIA 2014
data.description:
This year’s FIM Motocross of Nations marked the 68th edition in style as a total of 14 Fox athletes were selected to ride for the country and battle it out in Kegums, Latvia.
Once again the pressure was on Team USA to come out on top with our own Ryan Dungey leading the pack, his 6th year as captain for the team. Chad Reed also made a return after three years to fight for Team Australia along with Max Nagl riding for Team Germany and Glenn Coldenhoff for Team Netherlands. Find out from the riders what makes this event so special and see what went down on the track.

Music:
Artist: CTZNSHP
Song: We’re All for Fire

Artist: Broken Bones
Song: Sun Gods in Exile

data.title: Fox Wake Presents | Rusty Malinoski We Live | The Extra Mile
data.description:
Rusty Malinoski has always had a different approach to the sport of Wakeboarding than most others. Rusty’s hard core work ethic, confidence and competitive approach has taken him onto winning many National and World championships throughout his career. Growing older now, Rusty still has that competitive drive and desire to want to win at any level and all the time. Rusty hasn’t let off the gas yet. He feels he still has more to share with the sport and his competitors.

data.title: Fox Presents | The Search for Sasquatch, The Beginning
data.description:
The hunt continues…..
Once thought of as a hoax, myth or legend, the Sasquatch is real. Sought after for its exquisite fur and incredible features, it hides in dark forests and wonders the mountainsides.
Rarely does it reveal itself, but the evidence exists. It’s out there.
And so, the hunt will continue…

Camera/Edit:
Ryan Marcus

Hunter:
Scott Wynn

Voice of Hunter:
Robert Zepeda
